245
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:42,180
They don't know what happened.

246
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:44,480
They trust that it perished and passed away.

247
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:49,540
But two of them, on a five-mile journey of breathing through those holes,

248
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:52,820
survived and made it to the open ocean.

249
00:16:54,380 --> 00:16:57,660
It was a wonderful story, and it was actually captured by some artists.

250
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:04,560
And one of my children's favorite books at the time was this story of the whales under the ice getting free.

251
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:06,680
The reason I share that is this,

252
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:10,220
that worship can be seen in many ways

253
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:13,660
like a string of those breathing holes for us

254
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:17,900
where we come and are provided by

255
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:20,420
and receive air again from our Lord,

256
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:24,280
take it in and then go back out to serve

257
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:28,400
because we've spent time breathing in our Lord.

258
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,880
Worship is like coming regularly

259
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,600
to those breathing holes and filling up again

260
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,190
and offering all that we are

261
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:38,450
and all that we've been through

262
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:40,130
to the Lord in our worship.

263
00:17:40,930 --> 00:17:43,230
I hope that visual captures something

264
00:17:43,230 --> 00:17:45,770
and you can use that in your own thinking about worship.

265
00:17:46,510 --> 00:17:48,990
You see, worship then becomes a place to affirm

266
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:51,650
who again is in control of your life.

267
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:53,660
It's not us.

268
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:55,020
It's Him.

269
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:58,420
And the regular gathering of the people of God

270
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:01,780
affirms again, He is God and we are not.

271
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:05,360
He is in control of our lives and we are not.

272
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:09,200
It's a time to give Him thanks,

273
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:16,280
to soften our hearts again to replenish from the life where things are not always so easy where we

274
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:22,660
get buffeted and bounced around by the world to come and to breathe in and be renewed and refreshed

275
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:31,260
from our lord that's part of the experience of worship at the same time god receives a blessing

276
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:41,210
as well as he meets with his people who give him praise both give and both receive in this dynamic

277
00:18:41,210 --> 00:18:47,900
of worship. As I hinted at, there is both a personal and

278
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:52,020
a corporate dimension to worship. We can give God glory

279
00:18:52,020 --> 00:18:55,760
and honor and praise alone in our study, alone in our

280
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:59,780
prayer closet, alone on the couch at home, and we can also

281
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:03,580
do the same in this context, together with God's people.

282
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:07,560
Private and personal, corporate, are both

283
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:11,680
expressions of worship. I love Daniel in chapter 6,

284
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:14,740
an experience where he is personally, one-on-one,

285
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:15,740
communing with God.

286
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:16,160
It says,

287
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:19,180
When Daniel learned the law had been signed,

288
00:19:20,620 --> 00:19:22,660
for reference, the law that he was not allowed

289
00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:24,160
to worship his God any longer,

290
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:27,000
but only the statue placed in the square,

291
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:30,400
he went home and knelt down as usual

292
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,420
in his upstairs room with the windows open

293
00:19:33,420 --> 00:19:34,280
toward Jerusalem,

294
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,180
and he prayed three times a day,

295
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:39,460
just as he had always done,

296
00:19:39,460 --> 00:19:42,460
giving thanks to his God.

297
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:45,780
I love that devotion of Daniel.

298
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,560
In the midst of challenges,

299
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,040
in the midst of struggle,

300
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:49,980
he goes home,

301
00:19:50,380 --> 00:19:51,360
opens the windows,

302
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:53,600
and he prays like he's always done.

303
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:56,080
A man after God's heart there,

304
00:19:57,280 --> 00:20:01,180
seeking the Lord in his own personal worship experience.

305
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,640
In the New Testament,

306
00:20:02,820 --> 00:20:05,500
we see over and over experiences like this.

307
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:06,580
Acts chapter 2.

308
00:20:07,870 --> 00:20:09,410
And they worship together

309
00:20:09,410 --> 00:20:12,040
at the temple each day.

310
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:14,620
They met in homes for the Lord's Supper.

311
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:18,200
They shared their meals with great joy and generosity,

312
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:21,150
all the while praising God

313
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:23,930
and enjoying the goodwill of all the people.

314
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:26,950
And each day the Lord added to their group

315
00:20:26,950 --> 00:20:28,790
those who were being saved.

316
00:20:29,590 --> 00:20:32,850
The young church gathering together corporately,

317
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,800
and I think it's interesting, they met daily.

318
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:39,950
We struggle to get here once every few weeks.

319
00:20:40,070 --> 00:20:40,810
They met daily.

320
00:20:40,810 --> 00:20:44,890
They couldn't not have experience together with God.

321
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:50,860
And they praised the Lord.

322
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:55,580
And God blessed them and added daily to the number who were being saved.

323
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,480
Church, I'd sure love to see that.

324
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:03,180
I'd sure love to see people daily being saved and added to this fellowship.

325
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:05,540
Wouldn't that be an amazing goal?

326
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:10,600
To say, Lord, may you see people come and find you in our midst.

327
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:15,740
I hope you're getting a chance to see how wonderful worship is.

328
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:19,700
I hope you're getting a little bit excited to start this journey,

329
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:23,120
to step into the raft and let the waters take us,

330
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:26,680
let the Holy Spirit take us on a journey with expectancy,

331
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:29,300
with excitement, wherever it leads.

332
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,740
And quite frankly, Lowell and I, as we meet and pray and work through this,

333
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:37,630
we don't know exactly what it's going to look like a year from now.

334
00:21:38,950 --> 00:21:40,410
That wouldn't be an adventure if we did.

335
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:43,870
We wouldn't really be relying on the Holy Spirit if we did.

336
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,300
That would only be our thoughts.

337
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:48,360
It would not be necessarily God's thoughts.

338
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:52,790
But we're going on an adventure, friends.

339
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,660
Now, why are we doing this?

340
00:21:56,660 --> 00:21:57,220
Why in the world?

341
00:21:57,300 --> 00:22:03,080
Well, six and a half, almost seven years ago, you took a big risk.

342
00:22:04,780 --> 00:22:07,840
You hired a young pastor, didn't you?

343
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:12,300
You were either spirit-led or nuts.

344
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,450
Let's go with spirit-led.

345
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:25,060
And since then, we've been embarking on a number of changes in our experience here together.

346
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:28,480
The first one was just hiring a young pastor and all that that meant.

347
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:33,280
The second one, we made some opportunities for different kinds of worship experiences,

348
00:22:33,380 --> 00:22:39,860
having two different services that we might just be relevant culturally to different kinds of people in the community.

349
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,700
That was our second wave of change.

350
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:49,420
third we renovated this entire campus facility to bring us up to date in terms of worship and

351
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:55,780
the tools for ministry fourth we implemented a whole new series of governing documents that

352
00:22:55,780 --> 00:23:02,100
empower us for the flexibility that the 21st century ministry is going to require and to help

353
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:09,630
us get people and their spiritual gifts lined up for ministry that's the four waves now we embark

354
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:11,760
on this issue of worship.

355
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:15,400
Now we get beyond documents and bricks and mortar.

356
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:17,540
Now we get down to our souls.

357
00:23:21,230 --> 00:23:24,810
And I trust that we all want what God wants for us.

358
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:29,070
I hope none of us say, I only want a little bit.

359
00:23:30,470 --> 00:23:33,610
I hope you all come saying, God, whatever you want for me,

360
00:23:33,910 --> 00:23:35,370
that's what I want.

361
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:38,390
And I believe that if we're open to worship

362
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:39,870
and to grow in worship,

363
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:41,990
that we're going to begin to take in more

364
00:23:41,990 --> 00:23:45,330
of what God wants for us and from us.

365
00:23:47,290 --> 00:23:49,450
And quite frankly, I think we all want to be

366
00:23:49,450 --> 00:23:51,730
all that we can be for God.

367
00:23:52,190 --> 00:23:54,610
And I believe, and Lowell and I together believe,

368
00:23:54,710 --> 00:23:57,430
that as we embark on worship renewal,

369
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:01,020
that that'll grow us and mature us

370
00:24:01,020 --> 00:24:05,420
and change us and deepen our relationship with God.

371
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:11,460
We tend sometimes to think worship is

372
00:24:11,460 --> 00:24:15,500
all that nice music that precedes

373
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:22,910
the expounding of the word as if worship was the music and the preamble to the preaching

374
00:24:22,910 --> 00:24:29,350
and it's easy for us to get sort of lulled into making sure we all pick the right songs and

375
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:35,810
and worrying about all the those issues and friends worship is all of this worship is our

376
00:24:35,810 --> 00:24:43,100
life lived before god and so we're going to be looking at this thing as a total it is far more

377
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:48,040
than just worship or just music and certain songs and certain styles.

378
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:50,140
It transcends all of this.

379
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:52,940
And we're going to look at it all.

380
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:59,120
And may our head and our heart respond to the living God as we do.

381
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:03,240
Our worship is a joyful response to a loving God

382
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:06,500
that created you, that loves you,

383
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:10,720
and wants to receive your praise back to Him.

384
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:15,420
And I believe that when we understand this in our heads and our hearts,

385
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:21,900
When we begin to really put all this into practice, I believe it's going to profoundly change our church.

386
00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:30,410
I believe it will profoundly mature us and deepen us, and I suspect even grow us as we go on this adventure of worship.

387
00:25:32,020 --> 00:25:33,340
So what do you do next?

388
00:25:34,020 --> 00:25:36,060
That's the question I want all of you to ask.

389
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:42,920
How do you individually now respond as we get on to this raft and begin the adventure?

390
00:25:44,590 --> 00:25:46,790
I'd like for you to make these prayers

391
00:25:46,790 --> 00:25:49,430
part of your regular prayer experience

392
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:51,970
as you're preparing for this series.

393
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:54,350
Number one, I'd like for you to say,

394
00:25:54,830 --> 00:25:58,390
Lord, make me open to what you want to do in my life

395
00:25:58,390 --> 00:26:00,930
and the life of my church.

396
00:26:02,780 --> 00:26:04,700
That's a prayer of submission, isn't it?

397
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:08,770
Lord, I want you to do what you want to do.

398
00:26:10,930 --> 00:26:12,990
Lord, show me where I need to grow

399
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:15,080
and let me not resist.

400
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:19,400
We can get in the way of what God wants to do

401
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:22,580
because we put it on the brakes and dig in our heels.

402
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:29,360
And we need to say, Lord, open me to trusting

403
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:31,140
and going with you on this journey.

404
00:26:32,550 --> 00:26:35,410
I know for some, the idea of not knowing

405
00:26:35,410 --> 00:26:37,550
where the adventure ends is unsettling.

406
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:42,120
Some of your personalities, that's just very difficult.

407
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:44,260
You like to plan, and that's a good thing.

408
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:49,450
But I've also learned that a walk with the Lord

409
00:26:49,450 --> 00:26:51,310
is not always planned.

410
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:56,750
And so I pray that we'd be open

411
00:26:56,750 --> 00:26:58,550
to letting the Lord lead us as he goes.

412
00:26:58,910 --> 00:27:00,950
Lord, forgive me for my obstinance at times

413
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:02,730
and my refusal to grow with you

414
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:04,850
as you want to shape my soul.

415
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:08,960
Lord, change my heart

416
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,940
that I might more deeply touch your heart.

417
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:18,550
And Lord, may you bless our church

418
00:27:18,550 --> 00:27:21,590
as we grow in worship together.

419
00:27:23,190 --> 00:27:24,410
As we grow in worship together.

420
00:27:27,310 --> 00:27:29,310
As the astronauts see things differently

421
00:27:29,310 --> 00:27:31,550
and are changed by their journey,

422
00:27:31,550 --> 00:27:35,250
May we be transformed by this upcoming adventure.

423
00:27:36,170 --> 00:27:38,610
And so all I can say in conclusion is this.

424
00:27:39,210 --> 00:27:39,970
Buckle up.

425
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:41,680
Hold on tight.

426
00:27:42,460 --> 00:27:46,340
And here we go on an adventure in worship.

427
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,320
Let's pray.

428
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:51,080
Lord God, we're strapping in, Lord.

429
00:27:52,580 --> 00:27:57,170
We want to go where you want to go because it's all about you.

430
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,020
So make us ready.

431
00:28:00,670 --> 00:28:05,150
Put us through the right training that we need to jump in and go and trust you.

432
00:28:06,190 --> 00:28:08,970
And Lord, I do pray, and Lowell and others and leaders,

433
00:28:09,130 --> 00:28:11,790
we are praying that you are going to just have your way

434
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:13,530
in some profound ways with us

435
00:28:13,530 --> 00:28:16,510
as we grow in our understanding of who you are

436
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:21,030
and how we might joyfully and with full excitement

437
00:28:21,030 --> 00:28:23,690
give back glory and praise to you.

438
00:28:24,190 --> 00:28:26,670
How we might meditate on you more effectively

439
00:28:26,670 --> 00:28:28,990
and focus in on you and give you praise.

440
00:28:29,390 --> 00:28:31,870
How we might fill our lives with even more joy,

441
00:28:32,250 --> 00:28:34,530
even in the midst of the tough times in life.

442
00:28:34,530 --> 00:28:38,400
may we still live in a hopeful expectancy

443
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:40,300
that you are with us

444
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:42,760
that you walk beside us

445
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:45,750
and that you want us to give you love

446
00:28:45,750 --> 00:28:47,790
and praise and glory

447
00:28:47,790 --> 00:28:51,760
so Lord I pray that you would come

448
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:54,020
and through your spirit prepare us

449
00:28:54,020 --> 00:28:56,240
for the things that you have for us

450
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,680
for the teaching

451
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,040
for the modeling

452
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:01,510
for the experiences to come

453
00:29:01,510 --> 00:29:05,160
and Lord may the end of this series

454
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:06,460
may the end of our year

455
00:29:06,460 --> 00:29:07,720
may the end of next year

456
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:10,600
may you grow us as a church

457
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:11,560
and mature us

458
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:15,790
and may anybody that ever comes

459
00:29:15,790 --> 00:29:16,970
within the walls

460
00:29:16,970 --> 00:29:19,030
or within the context

461
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:20,890
of experiencing your people here

462
00:29:20,890 --> 00:29:22,790
may they know

463
00:29:22,790 --> 00:29:25,120
that this church

464
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,880
knows and worships

465
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:30,280
the living and the loving God.

466
00:29:34,190 --> 00:29:35,510
So here we are Lord, we're ready.

467
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:40,660
Lead us and take us as you please

468
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:45,550
and be glorified in the journey.

469
00:29:46,940 --> 00:29:47,940
We pray these things

470
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:50,400
in the authority and the power

471
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:53,680
and by the blood of Jesus, amen.

